ng\">six basic types of web hosting services</a>: Shared Hosting, Virtual Private Server (VPS), Dedicated Server, Cloud Hosting, Managed Hosting, and Colocation. The type you should get depends on what functionalities your business needs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Note: </em></strong><em>Some web hosting companies use â€œshared hostingâ€ and â€œmanaged hostingâ€ somewhat interchangeably, so they may say â€œsharedâ€ when they actually mean â€œmanaged.â€ Be sure to read the fine print.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Below, you can learn a bit about the different types of WordPress hosting options available, including which (if any) of our favorites offer these plans. Weâ€™ve left out colocation because itâ€™s just a rented space rather than a host in and of itself.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-container-627198448f3c0 wp-block-group is-style-decorated\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table alignfull is-style-stripes\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Type</strong></td><td><strong>Description</strong></td><td><strong>Best For</strong></td><td><strong>Offered By</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Shared WordPress Hosting</strong></td><td>Site shares servers with other sites using the same resources (RAM, CPU, etc.); often come with valuable tools</td><td>Startups with entry-level needs on a budget</td><td><a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"A2 Hosting\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/a2-hosting/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">A2 Hosting</a><br><a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Bluehost\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/bluehost/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">Bluehost </a><br><a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"DreamHost\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/dreamhost/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">DreamHost</a><br><a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"GreenGeeks\" href=\"https://aioseo.